# Badge System

## Server-Side Award (`@/utils/badges`)

Call the appropriate check function after a relevant action in an API route:
```typescript
import { checkAndAwardTaskBadges } from "@/utils/badges";
const newBadges = await checkAndAwardTaskBadges(userId);
return NextResponse.json({ entry, newBadges });
```

Available functions:
- `checkAndAwardTaskBadges(userId)` — 5/10/20/100 completed tasks
- `checkAndAwardBlogBadges(userId)` — 1/3/5/10 blog posts
- `checkAndAwardAdventureBadges(userId)` — 1 adventure
- `checkAndAwardLoonBadges(userId)` — 1/5/10/25 loon observations
- `checkAndAwardFeedbackBadges(userId)` — 1/3/5/10 feedback reports
- `checkAndAwardMembershipBadges(userId)` — 1/2/3/5/10 year membership
- `awardGuestbookBadge(userId)` — guestbook signer

Each returns `string[]` of newly awarded badge keys (empty if none).

## Client-Side Toasts (`@/utils/badges-client`)

In hooks, after a successful API call that returns `newBadges`:
```typescript
import { emitBadgesEarned } from "@/utils/badges-client";
if (data.newBadges?.length) emitBadgesEarned(data.newBadges);
```
`BadgeClaimHandler` (in root layout) listens for `badgesEarned` events and shows toasts.

## Badge Definitions (`@/lib/badge-definitions`)

`BADGE_DEFINITIONS` maps badge keys to `{ name, description, icon }`. Use `getBadgeInfo(key)` for display.
All badge keys: OG, TASK_ROOKIE/WARRIOR/MASTER/LEGEND, GUESTBOOK_SIGNER, BLOGGER_FIRST/CONTRIBUTOR/WRITER/AUTHOR, FEEDBACK_FIRST/CONTRIBUTOR/ADVOCATE/CHAMPION, MEMBER_1-10_YEARS, ADVENTURER_FIRST, LOON_SPOTTER/WATCHER/TRACKER/RANGER.
